The Android app is built with [Kivy](https://kivy.org/), a Python framework for cross-platform touch interfaces. It is packaged as an APK using [buildozer](https://github.com/kivy/buildozer).

## Structure

```
mobile/
├── app.py              # OnTrackMobileApp — Kivy application entry
└── screens/
    ├── home.py         # Address input screen
    ├── results.py      # Route results screen
    └── settings.py     # Configuration screen
```

## Key Differences from Desktop

| Feature | Desktop | Android |
|---------|---------|---------|
| GUI framework | CustomTkinter | Kivy |
| TSP solver | OR-Tools (primary) | Nearest-neighbor only |
| File picker | Native OS dialog | Android file intent |
| Map preview | Folium (HTML) | Opens in Maps app |

OR-Tools is not available on Android because python-for-android lacks an OR-Tools recipe. The nearest-neighbor fallback is used instead — it produces good results for typical field routes.

## Building the APK

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.11+
- buildozer (`pip install buildozer`)
- Android SDK and NDK (buildozer downloads these automatically on first build)
- Java JDK 17

### Build Commands

```bash
cd ontrack

# Debug APK (faster build, larger file)
buildozer android debug

# Release APK (optimized, requires signing)
buildozer android release

# Deploy to connected device
buildozer android debug deploy run
```

The first build takes 15-30 minutes as buildozer downloads the Android SDK, NDK, and compiles all Python dependencies.

### buildozer.spec

Key settings in `buildozer.spec`:

```ini
[app]
title = OnTrack
package.name = ontrack
package.domain = ai.qompass
source.include_exts = py,png,jpg,json,csv,txt
requirements = python3,kivy,requests,geopy,python-dotenv
android.permissions = INTERNET
```

## Testing Android-Specific Code

The CI pipeline validates Android configuration without building a full APK:

```bash
# Run Android-marked tests
pytest -m android

# Validate buildozer.spec parsing
python -c "import configparser; c = configparser.ConfigParser(); c.read('buildozer.spec')"
```
